This article is about an executive order issued by President Donald Trump on December 22, 2017, regarding the pay systems and salaries of various positions in the United States government. The order sets forth the rates of basic pay for statutory pay systems, senior executives in the Senior Executive Service, certain executive, legislative, and judicial positions, members of the uniformed services, and administrative law judges. It also establishes locality-based comparability payments and specifies effective dates for the different schedules. The executive order supersedes a previous order issued in 2016.